### Cellbyte: Revolutionizing Pharmaceutical Drug Launches

**Introduction**  
Founded in 2024 and part of the Y Combinator Batch W22, Cellbyte is transforming how pharmaceutical companies approach drug launches. Based in Munich, Germany, this nimble startup is on a mission to serve as a copilot for Pricing & Market Access (P&MA) teams, harnessing the power of artificial intelligence.

**What They Do**  
At its core, Cellbyte is an AI-driven tool designed to simplify complex data analyses in the pharmaceutical domain. It allows users to quickly analyze clinical, regulatory, and pricing-related data, unlocking insights from extensive industry documents with mere natural language queries. This means that what used to take hours or even days can now be done in seconds. By reducing research time and effort significantly, Cellbyte is giving teams the agility they need to outperform in drug launch strategies.

**The Founders**  
The brain behind Cellbyte are Daniel, Felix, and Samuel—three serial entrepreneurs who boast over five years of combined experience in the pharmaceutical industry. Their rich backgrounds equip them with the insights necessary to tackle the challenges faced by P&MA teams and to innovate effectively in this vital sector.

**Team and Partnerships**  
Currently, Cellbyte operates with a small but dedicated team of three employees. They work closely with their group partner, nan, to accelerate their development and outreach.

**Tags and Focus Areas**  
Cellbyte is categorized under several key tags that highlight its technological and industry focus: artificial intelligence, data science, healthcare IT, and databases. This broad scope demonstrates their commitment to leveraging cutting-edge technology for impactful healthcare applications.

**Conclusion**  
In a world where speed and precision are critical, Cellbyte is poised to be a game-changer in the pharmaceutical industry. By combining AI-driven insights with a deep understanding of market needs, they are setting the stage for more efficient and successful drug launches. For more information, visit their website: [Cellbyte](https://www.cellbyte.com/).
